[src:tensor-calculus/metric-tensor] Since g is symmetric as a bilinear mapping, it follows that *g*⊗ is a symmetric tensor.
[src:tensor-calculus/metric-tensor] More generally, one may speak of a metric in a vector bundle.
[src:tensor-calculus/metric-tensor] Using duality as above, a metric is often identified with a section of the tensor product bundle *E** ⊗ *E**.
[src:tensor-calculus/metric-tensor] The metric tensor gives a natural isomorphism from the tangent bundle to the cotangent bundle, sometimes called the musical isomorphism.
